PROS:
1. Open source

2. supports multiple languages:
java ,c# , .net , python, perl,ruby , javascript

3. supports all the platforms/os
Windows,Mac OS,Linux,Unix

4.Cross browser testing
CHROME FF SAFARI IE OPERA

5. headless browser 
PhantomJS HTMLUNITDRIVER CHROMEHeadless

6. Can be integrated with any open source unit testing frame work
TestNG T-Unit -->TDD

7. BDD Frame-work
Cucumber JBehave Serenity

8. Light Weight 

9.Available in the forms of APIs

10. CI-CD
Jenkins

11. csn be executed on local machine as well as on cloud/vm/servers
BrowserStack SaucseLabs AWS Docker

12. customize Web-Driver code base-->source code will be shared

13.Wrappers: Appium, Protector, Watir ,Robot Framework

CONS;
1. AS its an open source, so no direction support

2. You need to know programming-->No Scriptless or codeless Automation

3. no desktop app automation support

4. no report for test results

5. for any extra work: test cases designing,report ,build ,CI-CD

6. no bar code/ no captcha




